    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: `uv cache stats` Subcommand\n\n**4 files touched** — 3 modified, 1 new.\n\n### What I found\n\n- `CacheCommand` enum is in `crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs` (lines 879–905). `SizeArgs` is already defined at line 947.\n- Dispatch is in `crates/uv/src/lib.rs` — `CacheCommand::Size` arm is at line 1181.\n- `commands/mod.rs` has a consistent `mod X; / pub(crate) use X::fn;` pattern.\n- `cache_size.rs` uses `diskus::DiskUsage::new(vec![path]).count_ignoring_errors()` — the new file reuses this exactly.\n- `CacheBucket::iter()` yields **10 variants** (Python is intentionally excluded). Their `Display` impl emits versioned strings like `wheels-v6`, `sdists-v9`, etc.\n- `human_readable_bytes` is already re-exported from `commands/mod.rs` via `uv_console`.\n\n### Changes\n\n1. **`crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs`** — add `Stats(StatsArgs)` variant to `CacheCommand` + new `StatsArgs { human: bool }` struct after `SizeArgs`.\n2. **`crates/uv/src/commands/cache_stats.rs`** (new) — iterates `CacheBucket::iter()`, computes `DiskUsage` per bucket path, prints `{bucket}: {size}` per line + `total: {size}`, guards non-existent bucket dirs with `path.exists()`.\n3. **`crates/uv/src/commands/mod.rs`** — add `mod cache_stats;` and `pub(crate) use cache_stats::cache_stats;` alongside the `cache_size` lines.\n4. **`crates/uv/src/lib.rs`** — add `CacheCommand::Stats(args)` dispatch arm after the `Size` arm, calling `commands::cache_stats(&cache, args.human, printer)` (no `preview` flag).",
